-- Direcional, Gerdau, Vale, Wal-Mart de Mexico: Latin America Equity Preview
-- Andres R. Martinez
-- 2010-07-08T08:18:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-08/direcional-gerdau-vale-wal-mart-de-mexico-latin-america-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Latin American trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses and share prices reflect the previous close.  
 The  MSCI Latin America Index  gained 1.7 percent to
3,823.76. In Brazil, preferred shares usually are the most-
traded class of stock.  
 Brazil  
 Direcional Engenharia SA  (DIRR3 BZ): The real estate
company’s contracted sales in the second quarter rose 69 percent
to 321 million reais. Shares of the real estate company fell 0.1
percent to 10.79 reais.  
 Gerdau SA  (GGBR4 BZ): Latin America’s largest steelmaker
said it will increase its investment in a steel mill in Brazil’s
Minas Gerais state to 2.4 billion reais ($1.4 billion). The
shares gained 2 percent to 24.05 reais.  
 Vale SA  (VALE3 BZ): The world’s biggest exporter of iron
ore completed it sale of minority stakes in the Bayovar project
in Peru for $660 million. The shares rose 2.4 percent to 44.59
reais.  
 Chile  
 Cia. Cervecerias Unidas  SA (CCU CI): Chile’s largest brewer
said second-quarter sales volume rose 9.7 percent to 3.56
million hectoliters. The shares gained 2.1 percent to 4,949
pesos.  
 Mexico  
 Wal-Mart de Mexico SAB  (WALMEXV MM): The largest retailer
in Latin America said same-store sales jumped 4.7 percent in
June. The shares rose 1.6 percent to 29.92 pesos.  
